        \BinaryInfC {$\beta  < \alpha  , P^\beta (y', z', x') \vee  P^\beta (z', x', y') \vdash  \bot $}
        \UnaryInfC {$\exists \beta  < \alpha .P^\beta (y', z', x') \vee  P^\beta (z', x', y') \vdash  \bot $}
        \LeftLabel {\small  $(\mu  L)$}
        \RightLabel {$\theta [x' \mapsto  0]$}
        \UnaryInfC {$P^\alpha (0, y, z) \vdash  \bot $}
        \UnaryInfC {$\vdash  P^\alpha (0, y, z) \Rightarrow  \bot $}
      \end {bprooftree}


    Notice here that if we wanted to perform a \mu -reduction at the first (\mu  L) rule instance, we would need to unfold the cycles again.

A repository of notes I've made for meetings with my supervisor, collaborators and others.



    1060mee-0008mee-0008.xmlMeeting notes: Reuben 14/04/252025416Chris Purdy
We discussed the current strategy I've been developing for unfolding cyclic proofs until they are inert for a particular proof variable, focussing on the case of unfolding a non-inert cycle that is nested inside an inert cycle.
This case is problematic because, using our existing notion of copying external cycles when unfolding, new external cycles which are no longer inert can be created in this process.
Reuben suggested that we restrict the problem further and require that the label bijections along cycles also satisfy:
       \forall  x . f_C (x) = x \vee  f_C (x) \text { is fresh}   
  where "fresh" in this context means disjoint from labels in the companion of C.1062mee-0007mee-0007.xmlMeeting notes: Reuben 17/03/252025318Chris Purdy
After submitting the "Distributive Laws of Monadic Containers" paper, Reuben and I caught up with the current state of the \mu HOL^{ex} work.
We first dicussed an example that indicates the different situations in which we might want to perfom a substitution:


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
    \newenvironment {bprooftree}
      {\leavevmode \hbox \bgroup }
      {\DisplayProof \egroup }

    \begin {bprooftree}
      \AxiomC {$\vdots $}
      \UnaryInfC {$E^\alpha (x) , O^\alpha (s\, x) \vdash  \exists  \beta . N^\beta (s\,x)$}
      \AxiomC {$\vdots $}
      \UnaryInfC {$E^\alpha (x) \vdash  O^\alpha (s\, x)$}
      \LeftLabel {\small  (cut)}
      \BinaryInfC {$E^\alpha (x) \vdash  \exists  \beta . N^\beta (s\,x)$}
    \end {bprooftree}


  We could imagine the cut (implemented with implication elimination) being reduced and inducing a substitution of the right-hand proof tree for O^\alpha (s\, x). There are four different possibilities that we identified for the structure of the left-hand proof tree, each of which require different handling before and during substitution.


    \usepackage {bussproofs, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs, amsmath}
